Create Dax Measures 10

After we are done with the table relationship, we can now start creating calculated measures.

  • Click on the red button above to download the Zip file that contains all "the DAX formulas needed" for the calculations.
  • Create the measures in the order displayed since the measures at the bottom require the ones at the top to be created first. 

STEP 1:

路         Select the table "Foreign Workers" 

路         Click the new measure button on the ribbon.

路         Copy .# of Cases = COUNT('Foreign Workers'[CASE NUMBER])From the Word File that you downloaded.

路         Paste it in the Measure bar as Shown Below 



路         Repeat Step 1 for each Calculate that are in word File "the DAX formulas needed".

路         After you are done, you should have a total of 9 measures as it shown below.
